# Navbar

## Source of Truth
agent-os/product/tech-stack.md defines stack decisions.

## Structure
Fixed at top, full width, z-index 50.
Three sections: Logo left, Links center, Actions right.

## Logo
- Image from public/logo.png using next/image
- Size: 40x40px
- On click: smooth scroll to #intro
- Dark mode: as-is
- Light mode: CSS filter invert(1)

## Nav Links
INTRO · ABOUT · PROJECTS · SKILLS · JOURNEY · CONTACT
- Each scrolls to its section id on click
- Use onClick with scrollIntoView behavior smooth
- Section ids: #intro #about #projects #skills #journey #contact
- Font: var(--font-display)
- Weight: 600
- Size: 14px
- Uppercase, letter-spacing wide
- Color: var(--text-secondary)
- Hover: var(--text-primary)
- Active section: var(--text-primary) — track with IntersectionObserver

## CONTACT ME Button
- Right side of navbar
- Pill shape: rounded-full
- Border: 1.5px solid var(--text-primary)
- Background: transparent
- Hover: bg-[var(--text-primary)] text-[var(--bg-primary)]
- Font: var(--font-display) weight 600 size 13px uppercase
- Padding: px-5 py-2
- On click: smooth scroll to #contact
- Transition: all 200ms ease

## Theme Toggle
- Sun icon in dark mode (click switches to light)
- Moon icon in light mode (click switches to dark)
- Use useTheme from next-themes
- AnimatePresence for icon swap animation
- 36px circle button
- Border: 1.5px solid var(--border)
- Hover: border-[var(--text-primary)]

## Scroll Behavior
- Default: fully transparent background, no border
- After scrolling past 80px:
  bg-[var(--bg-primary)]/80 backdrop-blur-md
  border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border)
- Transition: smooth 300ms
- Track with useEffect + window scroll listener

## Mobile (below md breakpoint)
- Hide nav links and actions
- Show hamburger icon (Menu from lucide-react)
- On click: full screen overlay
  - bg-[var(--bg-primary)]
  - All 6 links stacked vertically centered
  - CONTACT ME button below links
  - X icon to close (X from lucide-react)
  - Animate with framer-motion: opacity 0→1, y -20→0
- Close on link click

## Active Section Tracking
- Use IntersectionObserver on all 6 section ids
- Highlight current section link with var(--text-primary)
- Update as user scrolls

## Rules
- "use client" required
- No hardcoded colors — CSS variables only
- next/image for logo
- lucide-react for icons only
- All scroll actions use scrollIntoView smooth